He was then cast in A Christmas Carol as Martha Scrooge, Scrooge’s Sister. Since 2003 he has had principal roles in Our Town, The Sound of Music, Godspell, and Arsenic and Old Lace. O’Neill played the role of Tommy Keohane in Brooklyn in 2007. His favorite moments of his involvement in performances at Saint Joe High since 2001 were as Eddie Carbone in Arthur Miller’s A View from the Bridge in Summer 2005 and in 2006 as Vincent Ginny in Juno, and most recently last Spring 2008 as Putnam in Arthur Miller’s The Crucible. He is attending Penn State this fall.

Senior: Jake Solich

Class: 4-09

Jake Solich is a senior and loves being a part of Saint Joseph’s High School. Graduating from Saint Joseph’s in 2004, he began his acting career in SJHS Theatre performing in many mainstage musicals in his sophomore, junior and senior year. Jake’s favorite Theatre memory was from his role in Joe Dipiero’s Pillow Talk in which he played the role of Thunderbolt which is one of the most demanding characters of the play. Jake played five different songs at once
